---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import "../../styles/pages/legal.css";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy policy · meemur"
  description="How meemur handles your data: what the contact form, newsletter, and analytics collect, who processes it, and how to reach us about your rights."
  canonical="https://meemur.com/privacy"
  pageClass="page-legal"
  ogTitle="Privacy policy · meemur"
  ogDescription="How meemur handles your data, in plain English."
  locale="en"
>
  <section class="section page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
      <h1>Privacy policy</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        The short version: we collect as little as we can, we never sell your data, and you
        can email us anytime to see or delete what we hold.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="container">
    <article class="legal">
      <p class="legal__updated">Last updated: June 10, 2026</p>

      <section id="who-we-are">
        <h2>Who we are</h2>
        <p>
          meemur is a boutique digital agency founded and run by Onur Yanar. This policy
          covers <a href="/">meemur.com</a>, which is hosted on Cloudflare Pages. For
          anything privacy-related, write to
          <a href="mailto:contact@meemur.com">contact@meemur.com</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="what-we-collect">
        <h2>What we collect, and why</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Contact form.</strong> Your name, email address, and message are
            delivered straight to our inbox as an email, and we don't store them in a database.
            Submissions pass through a Cloudflare Turnstile spam check before they're sent.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Newsletter.</strong> If you subscribe in the footer, we receive your
            email address and keep it only to send you occasional tips. Unsubscribe anytime
            by emailing us or replying to any newsletter.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Analytics.</strong> We use Google Analytics 4 (loaded via Google Tag
            Manager) to understand how the site is used: pages visited, approximate
            location, and device type. We look at this data in aggregate; it doesn't tell us
            who you are.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Hosting and security.</strong> Cloudflare processes technical data such
            as IP addresses in server logs to serve the site and protect it from abuse.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="cookies">
        <h2>Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          The only cookies we set ourselves come from Google Analytics, which uses them to
          recognize repeat visits. You can block or delete cookies in your browser settings,
          or opt out of Google Analytics entirely with Google's
          <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" rel="noopener" target="_blank"
            >browser add-on</a
          >. The site works fine without cookies.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="sharing">
        <h2>Who we share data with</h2>
        <p>
          Nobody, beyond the services that run the site on our behalf: Cloudflare (hosting
          and spam protection), Google (analytics), and Resend (delivers form submissions to
          our inbox as email). We never sell your data, and this site runs no advertising
          trackers.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="retention">
        <h2>How long we keep it</h2>
        <p>
          Messages you send us are kept in our inbox like any business correspondence.
          Newsletter addresses are kept until you unsubscribe. Analytics data is retained by
          Google Analytics for up to 14 months, then deleted automatically.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="your-rights">
        <h2>Your rights</h2>
        <p>
          Wherever you are (including under the EU's GDPR and Türkiye's KVKK), you can ask
          us what data we hold about you, have it corrected or deleted, or object to how
          it's used. Email <a href="mailto:contact@meemur.com">contact@meemur.com</a> and we'll
          sort it out within a few days, no forms required.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section id="changes">
        <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
        <p>
          If we change how the site handles data (say, a new analytics tool or a real
          mailing-list provider), we'll update this page and the date at the top.
        </p>
      </section>
    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
